- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is likely because the paper evaluates the performance of the method on a variety of real world graphs and proposes a parallel model for evaluating potential parallelism. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is likely because the method involves the random sampling and update of fundamental cycles in a graph, which is a geometric concept. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is possible because Laplacian linear systems are commonly used in network analysis. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is possible because the paper proposes a parallel model for the method and explores potential parallelism.
